  "prompt": "Buying life insurance at age 60. What should I be careful for?",
  "response": "When buying life insurance at age 60, consider these key points:\n\n1. Premium Costs\n- Premiums will be significantly higher than at younger ages\n- Rates increase rapidly after 60\n- Whole life policies are much more expensive\n\n2. Policy Types\n- Term life may be less cost-effective\n- Guaranteed universal life might be more suitable\n- Whole life policies could provide lifelong coverage\n\n3. Health Considerations\n- Medical exam results heavily impact rates\n- Pre-existing conditions can increase premiums\n- Some policies offer no-exam options\n\n4. Coverage Amount\n- Assess current financial obligations\n- Consider final expenses\n- Evaluate remaining mortgage or debt\n- Think about legacy/inheritance goals\n\n5. Beneficiary Planning\n- Clearly designate beneficiaries\n- Consider tax implications\n- Update beneficiary designations periodically\n\n6. Additional Factors\n- Compare multiple insurance providers\n- Read policy details carefully\n- Consider riders for critical illness or long-term care\n- Check conversion options\n- Understand waiting periods\n\n7. Financial Strategy\n- Consider how insurance fits into overall retirement plan\n- Evaluate if investment in other vehicles might be more beneficial\n- Consult financial advisor for personalized advice\n\nRecommendation: Work with an independent insurance broker who can compare multiple options.",
